<chapter xml:id="ch-I-6-Exponential_and_Logarithmic_Functions" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Exponential and Logarithmic Functions</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>This chapter establishes the exponential growth model, 
      connecting it to geometric sequences. Applications of the exponential growth model, 
      such as Continuously <xref ref="sec-6-4-Compounding_Interest" text="title"/>, 
      <xref ref="sec-6-5-Radioactive_Decay" text="title"/> and 
      <xref ref="sec-6-6-Newtons_Law_of_Cooling" text="title"/> 
      are emphasized. <xref ref="sec-6-1-The_Logarithm_Function" text="title"/> 
      is defined as a tool to solve for certain 
      parameters in the exponential growth model and the 
      <xref ref="sec-6-2-Properties_of_Logarithms" text="title"/> are presented.</p>
  </introduction>

